ergy to kinetic, thermal, and non-thermal energy (Yamada et al.
2010). Another example is that weakly collisional plasmas are often
observed to be in a strongly turbulent state (Federrath et al. 2010;
Bruno & Carbone 2016; Narita 2018; Beresnyak 2019; Fraternale
et al. 2019). Hence, they are characterized by the cross-scale transfer
of fluctuation energy from large injection scales to smaller, kinetic
scales, where energy dissipation is expected to occur (Schekochihin
et al. 2009; Howes 2015b; Matthaeus et al. 2015; Vaivads et al. 2016;
Verscharen et al. 2019). These features have, at least, two profound
implications."
